00:37:53,519 --> 00:37:57,459
chance to try the Everest demo, but without depth of field, do

639
00:37:57,459 --> 00:38:02,060
you find that anybody, like, you don't feel it as real as it

640
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:03,961
should be? Because obviously you have natural depth of field

641
00:38:03,961 --> 00:38:07,781
with your real vision without it being present in the demo. Is

642
00:38:07,781 --> 00:38:08,801
there like a disconnect there?

643
00:38:08,801 --> 00:38:09,222
Well, it depends. From

644
00:38:14,975 --> 00:38:17,383
From my experience, you as a real person,

645
00:38:17,383 --> 00:38:19,691
you don't really experience depth of field.

646
00:38:21,022 --> 00:38:24,584
because usually your eyes are always adapting.

647
00:38:24,584 --> 00:38:24,764
Yeah, yeah.

648
00:38:24,764 --> 00:38:27,626
So it's more like a movie trick where people use that

649
00:38:27,626 --> 00:38:31,408
to sort of change the plane of interest.

650
00:38:31,408 --> 00:38:33,690
But in our case, first, of course,

651
00:38:33,690 --> 00:38:35,931
the panorama is often very far away,

652
00:38:35,931 --> 00:38:38,432
so there is really not so much depth of field.

653
00:38:38,432 --> 00:38:41,174
And then we do have some atmospheric fog

654
00:38:41,174 --> 00:38:44,356
that sort of simulates the effect of distance,

655
00:38:44,356 --> 00:38:46,637
and I guess maybe that sort of works

656
00:38:46,637 --> 00:38:48,719
in a similar way as depth of field.

657
00:38:48,719 --> 00:38:49,579
